@startuml
title Viaverse Capability — Use Case Diagram
left to right direction

actor "Authenticated Account" as Account
actor "Business Owner" as BusinessOwner
actor "Admin / Trust Ops" as Admin

rectangle "Account Capability / Mode Boundary" {
  usecase "View available modes" as ViewModes
  usecase "Use Personal Mode" as Personal
  usecase "Enable Work Mode" as Work
  usecase "Complete worker onboarding" as WorkerOnboarding
  usecase "Start Business Mode" as StartBusiness
  usecase "Create business profile" as CreateBusiness
  usecase "Manage business team roles" as TeamRoles
  usecase "Switch active mode" as SwitchMode
  usecase "Check capability eligibility" as Eligibility
  usecase "Suspend capability" as Suspend
  usecase "Revoke capability" as Revoke
}

Account --> ViewModes
ViewModes --> Personal
Account --> Work
Work ..> WorkerOnboarding : <<include>>
Account --> StartBusiness
StartBusiness ..> CreateBusiness : <<include>>
BusinessOwner --> TeamRoles
Personal --> SwitchMode
WorkerOnboarding --> SwitchMode
CreateBusiness --> SwitchMode
SwitchMode --> Eligibility
Admin --> Suspend
Admin --> Revoke
Suspend ..> Eligibility : affects

note bottom
Core rule:
One Account can have multiple capabilities.
Personal / Work / Business are modes over capabilities, not separate user identities.
end note
@enduml
